PAUL KICHINKO v. E. W. SCARBOROUGH, as Director of the State Beverage Department. 20 So. (2nd) 127

June Term, 1944

December 19, 1944 En Banc Hoffman & Durant and J. Lewis Hall, for relator. J. Turner Butler, for respondent. *359PER CURIAM:

The record and the briefs in this cause have been.examined and the peremptory writ of mandamus is awarded on authority of Singer, et al., v. Scarborough, decided this date, a like question being involved in both cases.

■It is so ordered.

BUFORD, C. J., TERRELL, BROWN, CHAPMAN, THOMAS, ADAMS and SEBRING, JJ., concur.
